13. Task for “Puppet Intermediate”

1. Using Puppet-master and client from previous chapter
2. Install puppet explorer and puppetdb on puppet master verify that your current client is connected
3. Create new environment called “prod”, which should install nginx, create new mysql “prod_mdb” database, new user called “prod_user” and grant “prod_user” access to “prod_mdb”
4. Create new vagrant vm install puppet client connect it to puppet master to your new prod environment
5. Get reports about master status from puppet report service.

Task results
Get familiar with puppet environments
Learn how to create new environment and add new nodes to that environment
Learn how to use Puppet explorer and reports.
